  "root_text": {
    "iti37:0.1": "Itivuttaka 37 ",
    "iti37:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti37:0.3": "Paṭhamavagga ",
    "iti37:0.4": "Somanassasutta ",
    "iti37:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti37:2.1": "“Dvīhi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme sukhasomanassabahulo viharati, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṁ khayāya. ",
    "iti37:2.2": "Katamehi dvīhi? ",
    "iti37:2.3": "Saṁvejanīyesu ṭhānesu saṁvejanena, saṁviggassa ca yoniso padhānena. ",
    "iti37:2.4": "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, dvīhi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu diṭṭheva dhamme sukhasomanassabahulo viharati, yoni cassa āraddhā hoti āsavānaṁ khayāyā”ti. ",
    "iti37:2.5": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti37:2.6": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti37:3.1": "“Saṁvejanīyaṭṭhānesu, ",
    "iti37:3.2": "saṁvijjetheva paṇḍito; ",
    "iti37:3.3": "Ātāpī nipako bhikkhu, ",
    "iti37:3.4": "paññāya samavekkhiya. ",
    "iti37:4.1": "Evaṁ vihārī ātāpī, ",
    "iti37:4.2": "santavutti anuddhato; ",
    "iti37:4.3": "Cetosamathamanuyutto, ",
    "iti37:4.4": "khayaṁ dukkhassa pāpuṇe”ti. ",
    "iti37:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti37:5.2": "Dasamaṁ. ",
    "iti37:5.3": "Paṭhamo vaggo. ",
    "iti37:6.0": "Tassuddānaṁ ",
    "iti37:6.1": "Dve ca bhikkhū tapanīyā, ",
    "iti37:6.2": "tapanīyā paratthehi; ",
    "iti37:6.3": "Ātāpī nakuhanā dve, ",
    "iti37:6.4": "somanassena te dasāti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti37:0.1": "So It Was Said 37 ",
    "iti37:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti37:0.3": "Chapter One ",
    "iti37:0.4": "Happiness ",
    "iti37:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti37:2.1": "“Mendicants, when a mendicant has two qualities they’re full of joy and happiness in this very life, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements. ",
    "iti37:2.2": "What two? ",
    "iti37:2.3": "Being inspired at inspiring places, and making a suitable effort when inspired. ",
    "iti37:2.4": "When a mendicant possesses these two qualities they’re full of joy and happiness in this very life, and they have laid the groundwork for ending the defilements.” ",
    "iti37:2.5": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti37:2.6": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti37:3.1": "“At inspiring places ",
    "iti37:3.2": "an astute person should be inspired; ",
    "iti37:3.3": "a keen and alert mendicant ",
    "iti37:3.4": "should examine with wisdom. ",
    "iti37:4.1": "A mendicant living like this, with keen energy, ",
    "iti37:4.2": "peaceful not restless, ",
    "iti37:4.3": "devoted to serenity of heart, ",
    "iti37:4.4": "attains the ending of suffering.” ",
    "iti37:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti37:2.1": "cassa → yoniso (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1); yonissa (mr) ",
    "iti37:3.1": "Saṁvejanīyaṭṭhānesu → saṁvejanīyesu ṭhānesu (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "iti37:3.3": "Ātāpī → anātāpī dve (bj); dve pādā (mr) | nakuhanā dve → kuhanā ca (bj); na kuhanā ca (sya-all, pts-vp-pli1, mr) ",
    "iti37:6.2": "paratthehi → apare duve (bj) "
  },
